1
00:00:00,034 --> 00:00:15,391
At this year’s CES show in Las Vegas, Nevada, crowds from around the world came to see the latest products built with artificial intelligence (AI).

2
00:00:16,331 --> 00:00:23,530
CES is produced by the Virginia-based Consumer Technology Association.

3
00:00:24,394 --> 00:00:32,290
It presents the latest electronic product offerings or features, targeting consumers.

4
00:00:33,130 --> 00:00:40,567
More than 138,000 people attended the event which ended last weekend.

5
00:00:41,527 --> 00:00:48,564
More than 4,000 companies presented products at CES 2025.

6
00:00:49,403 --> 00:00:57,244
Here is a look at some of the top products shown at this year’s 2025 show:

7
00:00:58,123 --> 00:01:09,958
CES is historically an event at which large electronics manufacturers introduce their latest and greatest televisions.

8
00:01:10,498 --> 00:01:12,576
This year was no different.

9
00:01:13,236 --> 00:01:23,709
South Korean TV makers LG and Samsung both announced new smart models with built-in AI tools.

10
00:01:24,668 --> 00:01:36,238
Others – including Japan’s Panasonic and China’s Hisense and TCL – also released TV models with new AI tools.

11
00:01:36,962 --> 00:01:52,957
Korean manufacturer LG said its latest models are equipped with AI technologies designed to autonomously improve picture brightness, sharpness and sound quality.

12
00:01:52,957 --> 00:02:02,294
The AI improvements are powered by the company’s own a11 processer technology.

13
00:02:03,218 --> 00:02:19,609
LG also announced new updates for its Magic Remote device controller, saying new AI tools were added to provide more detailed search and interactive possibilities with users.

14
00:02:20,448 --> 00:02:31,502
Samsung introduced a system called Samsung Vision AI for its line of OLED and QLED TV models.

15
00:02:32,438 --> 00:02:49,502
The company said the AI tools are meant to turn the TVs into more “intelligent” assistive devices and to help “simplify and enrich everyday living” for its users.

16
00:02:50,401 --> 00:03:02,403
One example is a feature that permits users to click on different screen elements to receive immediate information about what they see.

17
00:03:02,403 --> 00:03:12,856
The company said another tool makes it possible to activate live language translations on-screen.

18
00:03:13,715 --> 00:03:25,738
Several companies at CES introduced robotic transport vehicles designed to travel over many kinds of surfaces or terrain.

19
00:03:26,517 --> 00:03:33,772
One model was built by Kubota, a Japanese maker of farm and building equipment.

20
00:03:34,591 --> 00:03:46,122
The company demonstrated how the KATR four-wheeled robot uses hydraulics to control the vehicle’s four legs independently.

21
00:03:47,050 --> 00:03:57,068
This design seeks to keep the robot secure and level even when working on hills or in rocky areas.

22
00:03:57,968 --> 00:04:10,846
Kubota says the vehicle – which is able to carry loads up to 240 kilograms – is small enough to be transported in most pickup trucks.

23
00:04:11,810 --> 00:04:19,447
Chinese developer Unitree Robotics showed off a dog-like robot model called Go2.

24
00:04:19,447 --> 00:04:27,225
The robot was designed with a series of cameras, sensors and AI tools.

25
00:04:27,785 --> 00:04:35,882
The company says this permits Go2 to make smooth movements and automatically follow its owner.

26
00:04:36,746 --> 00:04:48,180
It is able to carry small loads on its back and can also be used in security operations involving businesses or individuals.

27
00:04:49,119 --> 00:05:00,713
Demonstrations at CES showed Go2 doing tricks, like standing on two legs, dancing and giving high fives to visitors.

28
00:05:01,352 --> 00:05:09,098
The company produces several other dog-like models, as well as humanoid robots.

29
00:05:09,837 --> 00:05:16,357
The latest flying car designs are also a yearly favorite at CES.

30
00:05:16,956 --> 00:05:29,555
But this year, Chinese automaker XPENG took its presentation a step further by introducing a combination truck and flying vehicle.

31
00:05:30,275 --> 00:05:34,794
The company calls the system a Land Aircraft Carrier.

32
00:05:35,370 --> 00:05:44,703
It includes a large transport van with enough space to transport a vertical landing flying vehicle inside.

33
00:05:45,542 --> 00:05:53,715
The idea is for users to be able to launch the flying vehicle from anywhere the van can go.

34
00:05:54,415 --> 00:06:00,610
The flying car is fully autonomous and can carry two people at a time.

35
00:06:01,570 --> 00:06:14,823
Chinese media reported the company – which also offers several traditional vehicles on its website – plans to sell the combination for about $300,000.

36
00:06:15,263 --> 00:06:23,978
XPENG said it will aim to increase production for all its vehicles in the coming year.

37
00:06:24,962 --> 00:06:34,517
California-based Aptera Motors demonstrated a new electronic vehicle model with a built-in charging system.

38
00:06:35,356 --> 00:06:45,690
The company explains on its website that the vehicle has solar panels on its surface to capture energy from the sun.

39
00:06:45,690 --> 00:06:59,464
When charged this way, Aptera claims the car can travel up to 64 kilometers in a single day without being plugged in to a power source.

40
00:07:00,403 --> 00:07:07,822
On a full charge, the company says the vehicle can travel up to 640 kilometers.

41
00:07:08,638 --> 00:07:24,212
Japanese drink producer Kirin Holdings introduced a new product that aims to strengthen, or enhance, the taste of salt in food products without increasing the amount of salt.

42
00:07:25,012 --> 00:07:30,590
The spoon-shaped device uses electricity to increase saltiness.

43
00:07:31,426 --> 00:07:40,982
The company says the tool – which can be taken anywhere – sends a weak electric current through the top of the device to food.

44
00:07:41,721 --> 00:07:53,416
French electric sports equipment maker SQ-Motors presented an all-terrain electric board that can move on roads and snow.

45
00:07:54,336 --> 00:07:58,114
The company calls its invention the Sternboard.

46
00:07:58,806 --> 00:08:03,344
It is a three-wheeled board with an electric motor in the back.

47
00:08:04,003 --> 00:08:10,800
First designed to be an electric skateboard, a version was developed to move on snow.

48
00:08:11,460 --> 00:08:18,616
The powered boards have reached speeds of more than 60 kilometers per hour in tests.

49
00:08:19,336 --> 00:08:23,114
But the snow versions are not designed for speed.

50
00:08:23,754 --> 00:08:29,991
They seek to provide users with the ability to go up hills or move long distances over level land.

51
00:08:29,991 --> 00:08:31,991
I’m Bryan Lynn.
